ID59,Glasgow Advertiser,Glasgow,Scotland,United Kingdom,1790,01,01,persuade,of the scarcity of money and general distress at Calcutta. The multitude are out of employ and who cannot get into any situations by which they might support themselves is truly deplorable. If a place falls vacant a croud of necessitious candidates immediately urge their distresses and it is certainly a fact that for one appointment there are thirty Englishmen who would be happy to obtain it so many have gone out lately to India for whom there is no employment.,economic migration;local economic conditions
